0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[[["$","div",null,{"className":"telemetry mb-3","children":"February 25, 2026"}],"\n",["$","h1",null,{"children":"One year of Claude Code"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"A year ago, Anthropic launched Claude Code. I've since consumed 10 billion tokens, mass-tweeted about it, and mass-customized it. Here's my setup and what I've learned."}],"\n",["$","hr",null,{}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Anthropic launched Claude Code on February 24, 2025. I ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://x.com/MaxGhenis","children":"tweeted about it"}]," three times on day one. A year later, it's my primary development environment, and I've mass-customized the ",["$","code",null,{"children":"~/.claude"}]," directory that powers it."]}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"A year in numbers"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"| Stat | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| Tokens consumed | 10.2 billion |\n| Messages sent | 520,000+ |\n| Sessions | 2,346 |\n| Tweets about Claude Code | ~33 |\n| Peak API spend (Aug 2025) | $5,861/month |\n| Biggest single day (Feb 7, 2026) | $505 equivalent |"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"I started on the API, paying per-token. August 2025 hit $5,861. On July 20, 2025, I switched to the Max plan ($200/month, unlimited usage) and added a second subscription on a personal account in February 2026. The $200 plan replaced a $6K/month habit."}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"My IDE journey followed a similar arc of simplification. I went from VS Code to VS Code + TerminalGrid (a custom extension for running multiple Claude Code sessions) to iTerm2 + tmux. Each migration stripped away a layer of complexity. The tmux setup I use now is three small config changes — the TerminalGrid extension was hundreds of lines of TypeScript solving the same problem worse."}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["I recently audited my ",["$","code",null,{"children":"~/.claude"}]," directory and ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://github.com/MaxGhenis/.claude","children":"made it public"}],". Here's the full setup."]}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"How it started"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["I went to ",["$","code",null,{"children":"git init"}]," my ",["$","code",null,{"children":"~/.claude"}]," directory and discovered it was already a git repo. One of my installed plugins had initialized its own repo there, and my personal config files were sitting alongside it, untracked. The ",["$","code",null,{"children":".git"}]," directory pointed to the plugin's remote. My files were just along for the ride."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"So the first step was cleaning house. I removed the plugin's git history, initialized a fresh repo, and started deciding what to track."}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"The audit"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Before making anything public, I went through every file. The ",["$","code",null,{"children":"~/.claude"}]," directory accumulates a lot: conversation transcripts, clipboard images, debug logs, session state, plugin caches. Most of that is ephemeral or sensitive and belongs in ",["$","code",null,{"children":".gitignore"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["What's left after exclusions is surprisingly small: a ",["$","code",null,{"children":"CLAUDE.md"}]," global instructions file, a ",["$","code",null,{"children":"settings.json"}],", five hook scripts, a handful of slash commands, a few local plugins, and a pair of shell scripts for secrets management."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["While auditing, I also noticed that 36 GB of stale repo clones had accumulated in my home directory from multi-agent work. PolicyEngine US alone had 10 separate clones for different PRs, each a full copy of a large repo. That's not in ",["$","code",null,{"children":"~/.claude"}],", but the audit prompted me to clean it up."]}]],null,"$L2"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"KXmaeNPs760jd9SEpzaTl"}
2:["$","$L3",null,{"children":["$","$4",null,{"name":"Next.MetadataOutlet","children":"$@5"}]}]
